<br>
Well lets say you're a wiz trying to kill a warrior in a dungeon (we all know it can't be done, but lets pretend he's low on hp from a mob or something <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). You begin casting, he runs around the corner, &quot;You can not see your target from here&quot;. He runs back, hits you for a round or two, you begin casting, he runs around the corner. See my point, it's like the water exploit. You HAVE to be standing still for 6.1 seconds or whatver to get a nuke off, he can hit you while running.<br>
<br>
Another example. If it worked with harmful spells, it's probly gonna be the same for beneficial spell. Cleric says &quot;CHealing %T&quot;, warrior runs around the corner chasing un snared mob, gets an add, &quot;You can not see your target from here&quot;. Cleric has to wait till the warrior is back in his line of sight before attempting to cast another complete heal, if the warrior can live that long...<br>
<br>
